class Solution {
public:
    int hammingWeight(uint32_t n) {
        int count = 0;
        while (n) {
            count += n & 1;
            n >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses bitwise operations to count the number of set bits in the binary representation of n. It iterates through each bit, adding the least significant bit to the count and shifting n to the right. This approach is efficient and has a low energy impact due to its simplicity and minimal memory usage.

